---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Getting Started" activeSection="getting-started">
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>
  <p>Set up and run the Booltools SEO Crawler locally in a few minutes.</p>

  <div class="docs-screenshot">
    <img src="/screenshots/home.png" alt="Booltools SEO Crawler running locally" loading="lazy" />
    <p class="docs-caption">The crawler running locally at localhost:4321</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Go</strong> 1.21 or later</li>
    <li><strong>Node.js</strong> 22 or later (for the frontend)</li>
    <li><strong>npm</strong> (comes with Node.js)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <h3>1. Clone the repository</h3>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/booltools/booltools-seo-crawler.git
cd booltools-seo-crawler</code></pre>

  <h3>2. Install Go dependencies</h3>
  <pre><code>go mod tidy</code></pre>

  <h3>3. Install frontend dependencies</h3>
  <pre><code>cd web
npm install
cd ..</code></pre>

  <h2>Running in Development</h2>
  <h3>Start the backend</h3>
  <pre><code>make dev
# or: go run ./cmd/server</code></pre>
  <p>The API server starts at <code>http://localhost:8080</code>.</p>

  <h3>Start the frontend</h3>
  <pre><code>cd web
npm run dev</code></pre>
  <p>The web interface is available at <code>http://localhost:4321</code>.</p>

  <h2>Building for Production</h2>
  <h3>Build the backend</h3>
  <pre><code>make build
# Binary output: bin/booltools-seo-crawler</code></pre>

  <h3>Build the SDK CLI</h3>
  <pre><code>make build-sdk
# Binary output: bin/seo-crawler</code></pre>

  <h3>Build the frontend</h3>
  <pre><code>cd web
npm run build</code></pre>

  <h2>Docker Deployment</h2>
  <pre><code>docker compose up --build</code></pre>
  <p>The app will be available at <code>http://localhost:4321</code> with the API at <code>http://localhost:8080</code>.</p>

  <h2>Running Tests</h2>
  <pre><code>make test
# or: go test ./... -v -count=1</code></pre>

  <h2>Development Commands</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Command</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>make build</code></td><td>Build backend binary</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make build-sdk</code></td><td>Build SDK CLI</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make build-all</code></td><td>Build both</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make dev</code></td><td>Run backend (dev mode)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make test</code></td><td>Run all tests</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make lint</code></td><td>Run go vet</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make tidy</code></td><td>Run go mod tidy</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make web-dev</code></td><td>Start frontend dev server</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make web-build</code></td><td>Build frontend for production</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>make clean</code></td><td>Remove build artifacts</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <blockquote>
    <p><strong>Windows:</strong> install Make with <code>winget install GnuWin32.Make</code></p>
  </blockquote>

  <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
  <dl>
    <dt>Port 8080 already in use</dt>
    <dd>Another process is using port 8080. Stop it or set the <code>PORT</code> environment variable to use a different port.</dd>
    <dt>Node.js version error during frontend build</dt>
    <dd>Astro requires Node.js 22 or later. Run <code>node --version</code> to check and update if needed using <code>nvm install 22</code>.</dd>
    <dt>Go module download fails</dt>
    <dd>Ensure you have internet access and Go 1.21+ installed. Run <code>go version</code> to verify. If behind a proxy, set <code>GOPROXY</code> appropriately.</dd>
  </dl>

  <h2>What You'll See</h2>
  <p>After running an analysis, you'll get a comprehensive report like this:</p>
  <div class="docs-screenshot">
    <img src="/screenshots/report.png" alt="Audit report example" loading="lazy" />
    <p class="docs-caption">Full audit report with SEO and GEO scores, issues by category, and export options.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Next Steps</h2>
  <p>Once running, try analyzing <code>localhost:4321</code> from the web interface to audit the crawler's own frontend. Then explore the <a href="/docs/sdk">CI/CD SDK documentation</a> to integrate SEO checks into your deployment pipeline, or browse the <a href="/docs/rules">Rules Reference</a> to understand what each of the 130+ rules checks.</p>

  <style>
    .docs-screenshot {
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      overflow: hidden;
      background: var(--surface-2);
    }
    .docs-screenshot img {
      width: 100%;
      display: block;
    }
    .docs-caption {
      padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      text-align: center;
      margin: 0;
    }
    dl {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    dt {
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-top: 0.75rem;
    }
    dd {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      margin-left: 1rem;
      margin-top: 0.25rem;
    }
  </style>
</DocsLayout>
